reviews.text:
Lovely peaceful station with a 3 minute journey to Shanklin and a nice ride to Ryde via Smallbrook Junction, a lovely stop for the steam railway. 

Lake is a quiet station with a short walk to the beach.

Unmanned  peaceful station with one platform for trains going in both directions, continuing to Shanklin  & then returning for the opposite direction to Sandown & continuing to stop at all stations until reaching the end destination of Ryde Pier for the Isle of Wight foot passenger ferry to Portsmouth Harbour Mainland.

Tickets are purchased on board the train from this station as there are no ticket machines or travel information boards available.
